        <article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43469143" data-cid="43469143">
    <div id="comment_43469143">
        <header data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:one-meter square"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:one-meter square<span> (0)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3655223&cid=43469143">(#43469143)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43469143" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>There are fixed costs to painting. For example, a one gallon can might cost about $25 and could be used to cover 120 m^2 of wall, but if you just want to paint a single square meter you still have to buy the whole can, and the brush. Not to mention supplies like masking tape ($3), overalls ($50), sand-paper ($5), and belt-sander ($200), and more. If you add this all up, I suspect that's how they came to the "same as to paint a one-square meter wall" figure.</p></div>
